# SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
#
# .gitignore for the T8 tree-sitter grammar toolchain.
#
# - node_modules/ is the npm install output; never committed.
# - tree-sitter-nsl.wasm is built by `npx tree-sitter build-wasm`
#   and uploaded as a GitHub Actions workflow artefact (and
#   attached to tagged releases) per Clarifications session
#   2026-05-05 Q2 → Option C; never committed.
# - bindings/ is the per-language binding output of `tree-sitter
#   generate` (Rust, Node.js, etc.) — not used by T8's VS Code
#   consumer (which uses web-tree-sitter against the WASM build),
#   but the CLI emits a placeholder `bindings/node/` skeleton
#   even when unused. Excluded to keep the committed surface
#   minimal; downstream T11 editor integrations may opt back in.
#
# What IS committed: package.json, package-lock.json, grammar.js,
# src/parser.c, src/grammar.json, src/node-types.json,
# src/tree_sitter/parser.h (tree-sitter ABI header bundled by
# `generate` for downstream C/wasm consumers), queries/highlights.scm,
# queries/locals.scm, SPDX.NOTICE.
#
# See specs/010-t8-tree-sitter-grammar/research.md §1 (CLI pin)
# and §2 (WASM lifecycle) for the rationale.

node_modules/
tree-sitter-nsl.wasm
bindings/

# Per-language packaging scaffolding emitted by `tree-sitter
# generate` when run without `--no-bindings`. CI invokes the
# generator with `--no-bindings` (per scripts/ci.sh
# `treesitter-grammar-regen-diff` sub-step) so these files do not
# appear on a clean run; the defensive ignores below cover the case
# where a contributor forgets the flag.
binding.gyp
Cargo.toml
Makefile
Package.swift
pyproject.toml
setup.py
.editorconfig
.gitattributes
